## Response Guidelines

Follow theses guidelines when responding to a user.

- No emojis
- No bolding or italics
- Provide a summary at the end

## Coding guidelines

- Follow DRY principles
- No comments, unless necessary to explain something complex
- Write self-documenting code

## Terminal guidelines

Follow these guidelines when suggesting or running terminal commands.

- Use `rg` instead of `grep`
- Read files in chunks instead of entire contents

## Testing guidelines

- No tests

## Documentation guidelines

- No emojis
- No bolding or italics
